What can JS DO? (see test.html)

1) JavaScript Can Change HTML Content:
    - One of many JavaScript HTML methods is getElementById().
    - The example below "finds" an HTML element (with id="demo"), and changes the element content
        (innerHTML) to "Hello JS":

            document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = "Hello JS";
        
        ðŸ’¡ JS accept both double and single quotes:

            document.getElementById('demo').innerHTML = 'Hello JS';

2) JS can change HTML attribute values:

        <button 
        onclick="document.getElementById('bulb').src='light_on_bulb_image'"
        style="width:100px">Turn on light</button>

        <img id="bulb" src="light_off_bulb_image" style="width:100px">

        <button
        onclick="document.getElementById('bulb').src='light_off_bulb_image'"
        style="width:100px">Turn off light</button>

    - Here if we click on button 'Turn on light', it will change the value of the src attribute
        of an image. That is, it will replace the image(light_off_bulb_image) with new image
        (light_on_bulb_image). And same goes for 'Turn off light' button.
    - The working procedure is same as before, 
        (i) First usinmg JS method getElementById(), we find HTML element with id = "bulb"
            which is <image>.
        (ii) Then we change the source attribute of <image>

3) JS can change HTML styles(CSS):
    - Changing the style of an HTML element, is a variant of changing an HTML attribute:

        <p id="chng">style of this sentence will change if you click.</p>
        <button type="button" onclick="document.getElementById('chng').style.fontSize='35px'">
            Click Me!
        </button>

4) JS can hide HTML elements:
    - Hiding HTML elements can be done by changing the display style: